UTTERANCE.TRANSLATION: 'My son told me that he prefers black pants.'
'John and Mary have a strange bike. Two people can ride on it.'
'The doctor told me that Mom was acting strange and that she better go to the hospital and stay overnight.'
'I told Dan that when he inteprets he has to stand; he can't sit.'
'John is a really good liar. I fell for everything he said. I'm sick of him.'
'If an interpreter comes, it will be a strange situation.'
'My nephew has strange shoes that have red blinking lights.'
'Yesterday I was on the bus and a strange man sat next to me and started talking. I just stared at him.'
'Next week, Paul will be very busy. He works as an interpreter all day and takes night classes.'
'Is today a good day?'
'I'm sorry, you have to wait. Sit over there.'
'Paul told me he can't interpret because his car broke down.'
'My brother works nights.'
'I like Land O' Lakes butter.'
'John doesn't have special biking shoes.'
'Sorry, the black shoes are gone.'
'Farms like the hot summers because it's easy to grow big vegetables.'
'Sorry, the store doesn't sell funny books.'
'Mary goes to the farm to buy fresh butter.'
'I didn't know that I was not allowed to sit on the table, I'm sorry.'
'I used to lie but I don't anymore. I regret lying.'
'Does the library lend out magazines?'
'It's weird because Mary told me she would be home around midnight but I think she won't get home until three in the morning.'
'Are you going to interpret tomorrow at the library?'
'The name of the farm is Roberts Ranch.'
'On hot summer days, Mary loves drinking lemonade.'
'Mary likes margarine but she doesn't like butter.'
